The paper deals with the performance of polar codes in an AWGN channel, which is a topic related to information theory and communication systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves algorithmic design and optimization, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves simulations and performance evaluation, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
